modules.description: This module represents and compares password match segments, detailing their type, position, entropy, and structure. It handles matches like dictionary words, sequences, or spatial patterns, each annotated with metadata such as length and complexity. Used to analyze password composition and compute strength metrics based on specific match categories.

This module evaluates password strength by calculating entropy and detecting patterns like dictionary words, sequences, and repeated characters. It returns a numeric score and a list of contributing matches, each describing the type, position, and entropy of the detected pattern. The child module provides detailed match segment analysis, enabling fine-grained inspection of password composition based on specific pattern categories. Use this to enforce strong password policies during user registration or password updates by analyzing both overall strength and individual match contributions.
